text: Man I can't wait to see Bolas and Ugin's planeswalker cards in this set.

Hopefully Bolas's is entirely centered around all the toys he's bringing with him, something like:

Bolas Unleashed, 4BRU

Planeswalker - Nicol Bolas (7)

+3: Create a token that is a copy of target creature in any graveyard, except that creature is a 4/4 black zombie.
-2: Search your library for a permanent card, put it onto the battlefield, then shuffle your library.
-10: For each planeswalker you control, target planeswalker you do not control loses loyalty counters equal to the amount of loyalty counters on that planeswalker. Non-mana activated abilities cannot be activated until your next turn.
It's really too bad the fight mechanic can't be used for planeswalkers. Although if there was ever a time for it, it'd be this set.
Also, with the planeswalker-in-every-pack thing, I am 100% that we are going to see the Rules Committee try out planeswalkers as commanders in similar fashion to what we saw with Unstable.
I hope so. I’m so ready for walker Commanders
I'm not at all, but I'm also not against trying it for a bit.
It's obvious that Wizards has been bugging them for it for forever, and this gives them a chance.
I'm also hoping it means another push on Brawl, as well.
Gavin has all but said that's the case, anyway.
More Brawl. More walkers. More commander. Everything. Try everything. I’d rather have them try things and take risks than not
I'm starting to feel like post-War is going to see some significant rules and/or design philosophy changes.
Not on the scale of 6th edition, but...something.

tails
That would mean they had to design 36 unique creatures on top of the rest of the set. That’s a lot, even compared to Innistrad sets, right?
Maybe they aren't all.  Maybe some of them only have minus abilities and die to activation.

Other thoughts, now that we have the (probably) full list of Planeswalkers:

• There are probably 2 colorless Planeswalkers in Karn and Ugin. (2/36)
• With that in mind, and looking at members that are usually monocolored, I would guess that we are also getting 2 monocolored planeswalkers for each color (W=Ajani/*Gideon*/*Nahiri*, U=*Jace*/*Teferi*/Mu Yanling(?), B=*Liliana*/*hooded dude*/Sorin, R=*Chandra*/Sarkhan/*Angrath*, G=*Vivien*/Nissa/*Jiang Yanggu*) (22/36)
• That then leaves us with a walker for each Guild (WU=Dovin, WB=Kaya, WR=Nahiri/Ajani/*Huatli*/Samut, WG=Huatli/Samut/*Ajani*, UB=*Ashiok*/someone new, UR=*Ral*/Saheeli, UG=*Kiora*/Nissa, BR=Angrath/*Tibalt*, BG=Vraska, RG=Domri) (32/36)
• That then leaves us with a strange number, if I'm correct... Four. That doesn't leave enough to go for either full shards or wedges, so my guess would be Wizards left room for something strange. 5 color Bolas, planeswalkers that flip from one color combination to another, etc.
heads

But some of this could also be way off. Wizards doesn't always go as full in on cycles as we think they will, Karn can actually use all 5 colors of magic, flip cards could result in who knows what kind of color combinations...

Legendary Planeswalker — Kiora
+1: Untap up to one target creature and up to one target land.
−2: Reveal the top four cards of your library. You may put a creature card and/or a land card from among them into your hand. Put the rest into your graveyard.
